{"descriptions":[{"id":1362,"title":null,"content":"\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eWhile sometimes the imperative can be formed with the verb alone, in most cases, the imperative (command) and optative (wish) moods are formed by using particles. The main particles are: \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eདོ་\u003c/span\u003e, \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eདང་\u003c/span\u003e, \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཨ་\u003c/span\u003e, \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཤིག་\u003c/span\u003e, \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཤོག་\u003c/span\u003e, and the construction \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eརོགས་གནང་\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e","source_url":null,"is_primary":true,"created_at":"2013-09-15 04:15:44 UTC","updated_at":"2013-09-15 04:15:44 UTC","authors":[{"id":"6","fullname":"Nicolas Tournadre"}]}]}